Hi Ryan — great questions, here are the answers:

1. HOW EXPIRE IS SET:
pipeline.expire() sets TTL on the entire hash key, not per field.
The TTL resets every time any agent sends an event. Redis 7.4+
supports per-field TTL via HEXPIRE — can you confirm our Redis version?

2. WHOLE BLOB vs PER EID:
Currently it is the whole hash blob. This is why we added the
LAG_STATUS flag + 10-hour filter in snapshot.py as a second safety
layer — it catches stale EIDs even when the hash TTL hasn't expired.

3. PER-EID EXPIRATION:
Agreed — we should do this. Two options:
  Option A (Redis 7.4+): use pipeline.hexpire() for per-field TTL

4. RETENTION WINDOW:
Crystal/Ed McCorkle — options are 7, 30, or 60 days depending
on their reporting and HR offboarding requirements.
